To anyone struggling with this  before you start trying all these methods that likely do more harm than good  it's better to figure out your skin type. Is your skin oily  dry or combination? Did you know your skin can be oily because it's dry? Your body could be over producing oil to make up for lack of moisture. Also you could actually be sensitive to chemicals/ingredients in those so-called wonder creams  cleansers  toners  etc. It could be that you are stressed and that's how your body is letting you know. As someone who has tried all kinds of potions  I only saw actual improvement after (as much as we all hate this) drinking more water  eating more fruit and vegetables and refusing to use products with parfum or fragrance in. (Do you know that fragrance/parfum can be an irritant?) Even among fragrance free products  there are some that I can't use. You won't recognise the difference until you stop using them for a while  when you try using it again you may feel how much your skin actually doesn't like it. At the end of the day also remember MOST people do not have perfect skin  after working as a photo editor for a magazine you realise why Photoshop was created. Those images you see of perfection in the media are a dream they are selling.

Hi  just wanted to say that this video is coming from a comedic point of view. Just imagine a stand up comedian doing his bit about degrees. Education is different in everybody's lives. Education provides freedom for some  education broadens mind for some and sometimes it is just about increasing your knowledge in a certain subject. Education is not just one thing  education is not just one degree  education is not just one subject and your education is not just in one paper. Education is something much more than that. And everybody has their own definition of education. Certain systems of education might not be the most engaging and motivating   but the learning is not only with the provider  it is also in your hands. If you hate studying or you hate school  sometimes it might just be your negative mindset about it. Do more research about what you're learning and see if you're learning it in a way you best understand it. When you have moved beyond your compulsory level of education  a degree is definitely not the only thing you have to do  there are many options. Yes it is true  these days a degree may not be the most viable option to get a job  because the job market is really tough and you already have to work really hard for the degree. Well  this just comes to show that a degree is just the beginning. Yup  a degree might be the best solution  but it is a start. At the same time  if your situation permits you to choose another pathway than a degree  I'd say find something that you like to do and are good at doing! The world is really your oyster:)
